body:
What about doing something like this:
```c++
void RPCArg::MatchesType(const UniValue& request) const
{
    if(m_skip_type_check) return;
    if (IsOptional() && request.isNull()) return;
    // Special cases
    if (m_type == Type::AMOUNT || m_type == Type::RANGE) {
        // Type::AMOUNT: VNUM or VSTR, checked inside AmountFromValue()
        // Type::RANGE: VNUM or VARR, checked inside ParseRange()
        return;
    }
    // Check and throw exception if type is invalid
    UniValue::VType type = ToUnivalueType(m_type);
    request.checkType(type);
}
```

So we define the univalue type error string only once (inside `Univalue::checkType`) and not twice (`Univalue ::checkType` and `RPCTypeCheckArgument`).
Which will let us not have to worry anymore about stuff like #26069 and remove `RPCTypeCheckArgument`.

